{
  "texts": [
    "PageRank TrustThe PageRank family of algorithms can be used to calculate account trustworthiness scores based on this signal.",
    "An account's PageRank Trust score is calculated iteratively using a weighted version of PageRank:τ t+1 i = (1 -α) j G T ji ℓ G T jℓ τ t j + α N, (1)where t is the iteration step, α is the teleportation factor.",
    "The intuition of this method is that accounts with many incoming links are trusted and therefore have high PageRank Trust scores, indicating high credibility.",
    "Personalized PageRank TrustInformation about some high-credibility nodes may be available.",
    "To incorporate this information, an account's Personalized PageRank Trust is calculated as follows:τ t+1 i = (1 -α) j G T ji ℓ G T jℓ τ t j + ατ 0 i,( 2)where τ 0 i is defined by:τ 0 i = ⎧ ⎨ ⎩ 1 |H| if i ∈ H, 0 otherwise."
  ]
}